small animal practice, in other words? There were

06:46.955 --> 06:47.776
some. There were some. There were some. But most of 
them, even then, were because it was a large animal

06:49.819 --> 06:56.909
practice. And you know, at that point in time and 
until this day,

06:56.929 --> 07:09.587
there is the perception out there among 
applicants

07:10.394 --> 07:14.920
that what we want is a large number of 
practitioners. And they go to the conditions

07:14.940 --> 07:17.644
committee. Well, what are you going to do? What 
kind of practice are you going to do? I'm going to

07:21.389 --> 07:22.631
have a large number of practitioners. Because 
they think that's what we want to hear. That isn't

07:26.176 --> 07:27.338
true anymore. It used to be. And that old image is 
still hanging on there. Right now we're looking

07:34.648 --> 07:39.034
for more researchers than practitioners. Where 
do they go, your research products, let's say?

07:43.806 --> 07:45.447
What kind of employment do they go into? They go 
into biomedical research of many different

07:45.467 --> 07:50.051
kinds. Is that where your best market is actually? 
Yeah. And this is where we need the most upgrading.

07:58.238 --> 08:02.722
This is where we get our technology also, is from 
the research side. So it's the research and

08:02.742 --> 08:04.483
development aspects. Yeah. I expect the public 
perception right now, too, is still that a

08:05.324 --> 08:08.987
veterinarian goes into practice. They go out and 
they're either a large animal or a small animal,

08:10.261 --> 08:14.246
but they are in practice. They don't see this side 
of it at all. People come here. We've got six

