Veterinary Medical Association

17:41.570 --> 17:58.194
helped, hindered, or whatever, the profession in 
Texas and the South? Could you sort of talk about

17:58.254 --> 18:04.944
the relationships between, say, academia, TVMA, 
TVNA, and the public? Just how you feel about it as a

18:04.984 --> 18:07.307
person. Did you join TVMA, for example, right away 
when you got here? Is that pretty standard

18:12.908 --> 18:15.991
procedure that most people join? Why? Most by far, 
not all. Why do they join? What are their

18:19.215 --> 18:22.658
expectations? Well, you need some kind of a 
professional organization, organizational

18:22.678 --> 18:29.266
structure.

18:31.868 --> 18:37.935
You need, we call it professional and call it 
professional Because we're supposed to

18:38.422 --> 18:43.148
self-impose what we do. We're supposed to clean up 
our own acts. We don't have a political clout

18:47.514 --> 18:54.684
somewhere that's saying, you do this. We're going 
to do it ourselves. That's the reason we call

18:58.890 --> 19:02.134
ourselves professional. We clean up our own 
house. We do our own thing. So in a sense, it is a

19:04.277 --> 19:06.420
regulatory agency. It is an intra-professional 
regulatory agency. In other words, not from

19:12.224 --> 19:16.709
outside, but inside. Regulating yourselves. And 
we need that. And all the way from the county to the

19:23.757 --> 19:34.129
district to the state to the American Veterinary 
Medical Association is the organization of the

19:23.757 --> 19:34.129
chain. And I don't know how we'd survive without 
that, because if we didn't have that, everybody's

19:34.666 --> 19:42.538
going off on his own, just doing whatever he wants 
to do, you know. And I can perceive that, boy,

19:43.560 --> 19:50.871
there'd be clashes, and this guy's doing this, and 
